      • replaceVariableReferences

        public static java.lang.String replaceVariableReferences(FMIModelDescription modelDescription,
                                                         java.lang.String messageString)
        Replace FMI variable references with the name of the variable.

        The FMI log method optionally takes a variable number of arguments and handles #TypevalueReference#, specially where Type is one of r, i, b or s. To print a #, use ##.

        This method is based on based on a method by the same name in shared/sim_support.c from FMUSDK.

        Parameters:
        modelDescription - The model description that contains the names of the variables.
        messageString - The string that has had the % directed processed. The input will be of the format "foo #r1234# bar".
        Returns:
        a String with the variable references replaced.
